          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">On a more <i>positi=
ve</i> note, I was surprised to see=E2=80=94and hear=E2=80=94that Sotheby=
=E2=80=99s new commission structure doesn=E2=80=99t seem to have hurt consi=
gnments. At the top end, where deals are bespoke, the reduced buyer=E2=80=
=99s premium has given Sotheby=E2=80=99s less negotiating room. At a time l=
ike this, Sotheby=E2=80=99s ought to have been able to move consignors to a=
n overall guarantee where the seller locks in fixed sums and shares in any =
upside. That would allow Sotheby=E2=80=99s to make some money for itself on=
 any overage. Unfortunately for Sotheby=E2=80=99s, in the case of the Mille=
r estate, the family is so fabulously wealthy that they opted instead for a=
 deal that would cut deeply into the house=E2=80=99s own revenue. <br/><br/=
>On lower-end property, where Sotheby=E2=80=99s stated policy has been to <=
i>not</i> negotiate enhanced hammer deals or introductory commissions, ther=
e has been
real consternation among the advisors who bring these consignments to the a=
uction house about the loss of their most-favored-nation status. Many predi=
cted Sotheby=E2=80=99s would have to start whittling away at their tough st=
ance to survive. All summer, there was speculation that Sotheby=E2=80=99s w=
as losing out on property to Phillips and Christie=E2=80=99s. Yet this week=
=E2=80=99s Contemporary Curated sale does not seem to have been hamstrung b=
y the policy. And in my conversations with Sotheby=E2=80=99s staff, some of=
 whom were deeply skeptical of the new policy, I was surprised to hear chip=
per views on the season and a sanguine attitude about the new fee structure=
 and negotiating strictures. <br/><br/>It=E2=80=99s far too early to say th=
at the new fee structure has worked. Folks in the Chinese art department we=
re chuffed about their strong sales last week. That may=E2=80=94or may not=
=E2=80=94have been attributable to the lower buyer=E2=80=99s premium, but t=
here are few enhanced hammer deals in that category. So far, however,
worst-case scenario predictions seem to be unfounded. Yes, the Hong Kong sa=
les had to be pushed back two months due to a lack of property lined up to =
sell. But that may have been more a function of the remarkable amount of st=
aff turnover in Hong Kong caused by a quiet bloodletting over the summer an=
d the return of some high-profile dealmakers who had been seconded to their=
 home ports. The new team barely had time to hang up their coats before the=
 deadline for a late September sale.<br/></td>
